# Protected Files

These files run real money, real auth, or schema migrations. **Never modify them as a side effect of another task.** Always:

1. Quote the user request that asks for the change.
2. Show a diff plan **before** writing.
3. Wait for explicit confirmation.

## Billing & payments (real money)

- `src/routes/stripe.webhook.js` — credit grants from Stripe events
- `src/routes/stripe.routes.js` — checkout / portal sessions
- `src/routes/crypto.webhook.js` · `src/routes/nowpayments.routes.js`
- `src/services/credit.service.js` — every credit add/deduct
- `src/services/stripe-credit-reconcile.service.js` — dual-account legacy/new reconciliation
- `src/services/voice-monthly-billing.service.js`
- `src/services/referral.service.js` — commission payouts
- `src/services/generation-pricing.service.js` · `src/services/video-generation-pricing.js`

> **Stripe is dual-account** (legacy + new US LLC). Never assume single-account behavior. See `docs/STRIPE_DUAL_ACCOUNT.md`.

## Auth & access control

- `src/middleware/auth.middleware.js`
- `src/middleware/admin.middleware.js`
- `src/controllers/auth.controller.js`
- `src/controllers/twoFactor.controller.js`

## Database schema

- `prisma/schema.prisma` — never rename/drop a field without explicit migration plan
- Anything under `prisma/migrations/` — append-only, never edit existing migrations

## Worker mirrors (synced from external repos)

- `runpod-mdcln-motion/**` — synced from `mconqeuroror/motion`. Edits must be made upstream and pulled.

## Generated files (do not hand-edit)

- `docs/generated/**` — regenerate via `npm run docs:registry`
- `docs/openapi/client-api.openapi.yaml` — regenerated by the same command
- `package-lock.json` — let `npm` write it

## If you must edit a protected file

State explicitly: *"This change touches a protected file (`X`). Do you want me to proceed?"* Then wait.
